<i>Like I said, the day started</i>

12:45.857 --> 12:49.226
<i>by being about bagels,
but that would abruptly change.</i>

12:49.228 --> 12:51.229
My weekly poker game
is moving to the Cobra Lounge.

12:51.231 --> 12:53.196
Tomorrow night,
and then every Tuesday night.

12:53.198 --> 12:54.331
You'll help run it.

12:54.333 --> 12:55.865
Take these names and numbers.

12:55.867 --> 12:57.468
Tell them to bring
ten grand in cash

12:57.471 --> 13:00.374
for the first buy-in.
The blinds are 51/100.

13:01.607 --> 13:02.940
- And Molly.
- Yeah.

13:02.942 --> 13:04.577
Don't fucking tell anybody.

13:11.750 --> 13:15.319
<i>I'd regarded Dean as a
nitwit when I regarded him at all.</i>

13:15.321 --> 13:18.256
<i>But on that pad were nine names
along with phone numbers of</i>

13:18.258 --> 13:21.459
<i>some of the wealthiest and most
famous people in the world.</i>

13:21.461 --> 13:24.594
<i>I put the numbers in my phone
and composed a simple message.</i>

13:24.596 --> 13:27.031
<i>There'd be a game tomorrow
night at the Cobra Lounge.</i>

13:27.033 --> 13:28.936
<i>There was
a $10,000 dollar buy-in.</i>

13:31.404 --> 13:33.573
<i>All nine players confirmed
that they'd be there.</i>

13:36.675 --> 13:40.076
<i>All within 90 seconds
of my sending the text.</i>

13:40.078 --> 13:43.481
<i>The Cobra Lounge sits on
the edge of the Sunset Strip.</i>

13:43.483 --> 13:46.450
<i>And in it's heyday was famous
for introducing unknown bands</i>

13:46.452 --> 13:49.519
<i>like "The Doors"
and "The Beach Boys."</i>

13:49.521 --> 13:52.056
<i>All I knew was school work
and skiing.</i>

13:52.058 --> 13:53.657
<i>I'd always figured
sophistication</i>

13:53.659 --> 13:55.660
<i>would be easy to learn
if I ever needed it.</i>

13:55.662 --> 13:57.662
<i>My cheese platter had
a sticker that read</i>

13:57.664 --> 14:01.232
<i>"Cheese From the Great State
of Michigan."</i>

14:01.234 --> 14:03.434
<i>Diego, a professional dealer</i>

14:03.436 --> 14:06.336
<i>was setting up the table
when I got there.</i>

14:06.338 --> 14:08.372
<i>I Googled "What type of music</i>

14:08.374 --> 14:10.407
<i>do poker players
like to listen to?"</i>

14:10.409 --> 14:12.209
<i>and then tried to figure out
how to make a playlist</i>

14:12.211 --> 14:14.244
<i>out of one Kenny Rogers song.</i>

14:14.246 --> 14:17.080
<i>I set up the bar...</i>

14:17.082 --> 14:18.682
<i>put out my cheese platter...</i>

14:18.684 --> 14:20.350
<i>and positioned myself
at the door where I'd been</i>

14:20.352 --> 14:21.618
<i>instructed to only let in</i>

14:21.620 --> 14:23.219
<i>the names on the list.</i>

14:23.221 --> 14:24.788
<i>I was wearing my best dress,
which I had bought</i>

14:24.790 --> 14:28.258
<i>two years earlier
at J.C. Penney for $88.</i>

14:28.260 --> 14:30.293
<i>The players started to arrive.</i>

14:30.295 --> 14:32.763
<i>I introduced myself as Molly,
Dean's assistant.</i>

14:32.765 --> 14:33.933
For you.

14:35.367 --> 14:37.203
<i>Asked if I could
get them a drink.</i>

14:40.807 --> 14:44.111
<i>And took from each of them
$10,000 in cash.</i>

14:46.578 --> 14:48.812
- Hi.
- Hi.

14:48.814 --> 14:49.982
I'm...

14:52.684 --> 14:53.917
I know.

14:53.919 --> 14:55.985
- Your boss...
- Everybody here?

14:55.987 --> 14:57.320
- Yeah.
- Hey, buddy.

14:57.322 --> 14:59.159
Fuck off,
I'm gonna own your shit.

15:00.425 --> 15:02.892
Ugly dress.
Ugly shoes.

15:02.894 --> 15:04.364
Let's play!

15:06.999 --> 15:09.532
<i>Diego fanned nine
cards out on the table</i>

15:09.534 --> 15:11.704
<i>and the players
chose for seats.</i>

15:21.179 --> 15:23.080
<i>Eleven and eleven...</i>

15:23.082 --> 15:25.282
<i>He checked,
the action's on you.</i>

15:25.284 --> 15:28.918
<i>I just finished
counting out $90,000 in cash.</i>

15:28.920 --> 15:33.791
<i>I was in a room
with movie stars, directors.</i>

15:33.793 --> 15:36.292
<i>Rappers. Boxers.</i>

15:36.294 --> 15:38.265
<i>- He's in trouble.
- And business titans.</i>

15:39.499 --> 15:42.399
<i>They were going all in,
all the time.</i>

15:42.401 --> 15:45.136
<i>Burning through their
buy-ins over and over.</i>

15:45.138 --> 15:47.504
<i>- Here you go. Good luck
- Thank you so much.</i>

15:47.506 --> 15:49.840
I don't know.

15:49.842 --> 15:53.042
<i>I Googled every word
I heard that I didn't know.</i>

15:53.044 --> 15:54.445
- <i>Flop. River.</i>
- Fourth Street.

15:54.447 --> 15:56.480
<i>Fourth Street. Tilt. Cooler.</i>

15:56.482 --> 15:58.648
<i>- Boat. Nuts.
- Yeah, he's pot committed.</i>

15:58.650 --> 15:59.651
<i>Playing the rush.</i>

16:02.521 --> 16:03.988
You keeping track
of the buy-ins?

16:03.990 --> 16:06.590
- Yeah.
- Where? Where's the paper?

16:06.592 --> 16:07.792
Spreadsheet.

16:14.332 --> 16:15.802
<i>Yeah, motherfucker.</i>

16:19.038 --> 16:20.475
All in.

16:22.308 --> 16:23.773
<i>The game ended at 3:30.</i>

16:23.775 --> 16:25.810
<i>And when it did,
that's when Dean shouted out...</i>

16:25.812 --> 16:30.947
Hey, tip Molly if you wanna
get invited back next week.

16:30.949 --> 16:32.583
<i>Tip Molly.</i>

16:32.585 --> 16:36.019
<i>Deep down, I didn't like
the sound of that.</i>

16:36.021 --> 16:37.521
<i>Deep down, I knew
that when your boss says...</i>

16:37.523 --> 16:38.822
- And Molly.
- Yeah.

16:38.824 --> 16:40.657
Don't fucking tell anybody.

16:40.659 --> 16:41.892
<i>That's usually
not the beginning</i>

16:41.894 --> 16:43.160
<i>of a promising law career.</i>

16:43.162 --> 16:44.697
See you next week.

16:47.098 --> 16:49.300
<i>But that was deep down.</i>

16:49.302 --> 16:51.303
<i>I just made $3000.</i>

17:16.928 --> 17:18.694
What are you reading?

17:18.696 --> 17:20.163
"The Crucible."

17:20.165 --> 17:21.763
For school?

17:21.766 --> 17:23.236
My father assigned it.

17:26.571 --> 17:29.240
Do you know how many witches
were burned at Salem?

17:29.242 --> 17:30.840
- How many?
- None.

17:30.842 --> 17:33.343
They didn't burn witches.
It's a myth. They hanged them.

17:33.345 --> 17:36.549
Or drowned them, or crushed them
with heavy rocks.

17:38.517 --> 17:40.251
Wait. Aren't...
You're Molly Bloom.

17:40.253 --> 17:42.218
- Right?
- Yeah.

17:42.220 --> 17:44.655
You don't look the same
as in your photos.

17:44.657 --> 17:46.126
None of us do.

17:47.293 --> 17:49.126
- Molly.
- Yes.

17:49.128 --> 17:50.660
- I'm Charlie Jaffey.
- Oh.

17:50.662 --> 17:52.629
Thank you again
for seeing me so early.

17:52.631 --> 17:55.032
- This is my daughter, Stella.
- We met.

17:55.034 --> 17:57.667
Isabel will be here in 45
minutes to take you to school.

17:57.669 --> 17:59.503
- Finish your math?
- Yeah.

17:59.505 --> 18:01.437
- Civ? You know it?
- Yeah.

18:01.439 --> 18:03.006
<i>Could you teach it
in class today?</i>

18:03.008 --> 18:06.409
If I asked you to teach me
Roman Law, could you do it?

18:06.411 --> 18:08.547
- Yes.
- <i>Okay.</i>

18:10.448 --> 18:12.484
So. First things first.

18:12.486 --> 18:14.407
When was the last time you
slept? Today's Friday.

18:15.418 --> 18:17.320
Tuesday morning at 5 a.m.,
I was arrested by the FBI.

18:17.322 --> 18:19.557
I spent Tuesday
in L.A. County Jail.

18:19.559 --> 18:21.257
I was assessed to be
a minimal flight risk

18:21.259 --> 18:22.993
and bail was set
at a $100,000.

18:22.995 --> 18:24.695
My mother signed over her house.

18:24.697 --> 18:26.696
I was released on Wednesday
and ordered to appear

18:26.698 --> 18:29.934
in Federal Court
in New York's Southern District.

18:29.936 --> 18:31.635
10 a.m. today.

18:31.637 --> 18:32.672
In here.

18:33.505 --> 18:35.175
<i>Close that, will you?</i>

18:38.843 --> 18:41.811
I flew here Wednesday and met
with five attorneys yesterday.

18:41.813 --> 18:44.715
Have a seat.
You didn't hire any of them?

18:44.717 --> 18:46.417
Three of them had
already been taken.

18:46.419 --> 18:48.551
Yeah, 31 people were named
in your indictment.

18:48.553 --> 18:50.020
It's Black Friday
for criminal lawyers.

18:50.022 --> 18:51.254
How about the other two?

18:51.256 --> 18:52.322
One told me money was his

18:52.324 --> 18:53.756
second favorite form of payment.

18:53.758 --> 18:55.224
- I know him.
- <i>The fifth was also taken.</i>

18:55.226 --> 18:57.461
- But he recommended I call you.
- Why?

18:57.463 --> 18:58.995
I told him I wanted someone
who'd worked in

18:58.997 --> 19:01.700
the prosecutor's office and
wasn't even a little bit shady.

19:04.035 --> 19:06.235
Do you know about me?

19:06.237 --> 19:09.039
Um, I've been briefed a little
by my daughter, who knows

19:09.041 --> 19:11.507
a lot about your story
because her mother's a moron.

19:11.509 --> 19:14.744
- Her mother reads the tabloids?
- Yeah, and I read them too.

19:14.746 --> 19:17.047
I read your indictment
after I got your call last night

19:17.049 --> 19:18.948
and I bought your book.

19:18.950 --> 19:21.185
I'm only on page 112,
but, Molly, did you commit

19:21.187 --> 19:22.953
a felony and then write
a book about it?

19:22.955 --> 19:24.355
I haven't run a game
in over two years.

19:24.357 --> 19:25.589
Not to spoil the ending,
but that's

19:25.591 --> 19:26.756
when the government
raided my game

19:26.758 --> 19:28.391
<i>and took all my money assuming</i>

19:28.393 --> 19:30.927
all of it was made illegally,
which it wasn't.

19:30.929 --> 19:32.963
I've been living in my
mother's house in Telluride

19:32.965 --> 19:36.699
and... I wrote the book so I
could start paying off debts.

19:36.701 --> 19:38.702
<i>I just finished the press tour
for the book and I moved back</i>

19:38.704 --> 19:41.672
to Los Angeles
so I could start over.

19:41.674 --> 19:45.341
Hm. You ran games in L.A.
for roughly eight years?

19:45.343 --> 19:47.511
- Yeah. Right.
- Without taking a rake?

19:47.513 --> 19:49.346
And then you ran games
in New York for roughly two.

19:49.348 --> 19:51.483
Well, I took a rake
for the last six months.

19:51.485 --> 19:56.119
In the first 112 pages,
you name a bunch of names.

19:56.121 --> 19:57.454
- Sorry?
- Uh.

19:57.456 --> 19:58.688
You named the names
of some movie stars

19:58.690 --> 20:00.991
that played in your game.

20:00.993 --> 20:02.525
Yeah.

20:02.527 --> 20:04.730
That not against
some sort of poker code?

20:06.931 --> 20:08.465
Am I supposed to be sitting
all the way over here?

20:08.467 --> 20:10.303
- Can you hear me from there?
- Yeah.

20:11.937 --> 20:13.503
Are you taking me
on as a client?

20:13.505 --> 20:15.505
<i>My retainer is $250,000.</i>

20:15.507 --> 20:17.977
Do you have $250,000?

20:19.145 --> 20:21.645
No. I don't have anything.

20:21.647 --> 20:23.080
What about the sales
from your book?

20:23.082 --> 20:25.483
<i>The book isn't
jumping off the shelves.</i>

20:25.485 --> 20:27.485
But I will find a way
to pay you, Charlie.

20:27.487 --> 20:28.854
Ask around about me.

20:29.988 --> 20:31.722
Unfortunately,
the people I'd ask

20:31.724 --> 20:33.624
are goin' away for a while.

20:33.626 --> 20:36.526
What happened on Tuesday morning
was called a "GPS Takedown."

20:36.528 --> 20:38.795
Thirty-one people were arrested
in the same instant.

20:38.797 --> 20:41.330
Something in excess
of 600 agents were dispatched

20:41.332 --> 20:43.032
to locations
in New York and L.A.

20:43.034 --> 20:45.234
<i>in coordinated strikes
with automatic weapons.</i>

20:45.236 --> 20:47.472
And you're trying to tell me
you're in my office

20:47.474 --> 20:50.307
because you raked a game
of Texas Hold 'Em?

20:50.309 --> 20:52.542
Have you seen the other names
in your indictment?

20:52.544 --> 20:54.845
"Nicholas Kozlowski.
Peter Druzhinsky.

20:54.847 --> 20:56.612
Peter Antonovich.
The Gershen Brothers."

20:56.614 --> 20:58.115
I mean come on, Molly,
just how deep

20:58.117 --> 20:59.449
into the Russian mob were you?

20:59.451 --> 21:00.986
Because your book doesn't say.

21:17.570 --> 21:20.436
Why are you making your daughter
read "The Crucible?"

21:20.438 --> 21:21.871
So she can see
what happens to a group

21:21.873 --> 21:23.674
of bored teenage girls
when they gossip.

21:23.676 --> 21:25.375
- I never read the play.
- Many consider it to be...

21:25.377 --> 21:26.810
The best play
of the 20th century.

21:26.812 --> 21:28.011
Is that what
many consider it to be...

21:28.013 --> 21:30.513
I don't defend
violent criminals.

21:30.515 --> 21:32.616
- I've never hurt anyone...
- Your friends have.

21:32.618 --> 21:34.618
I've never heard of 90%
of the names...

21:34.620 --> 21:35.718
- On the indictment.
- And the other 10%?

21:35.720 --> 21:36.820
I didn't know they were
connected.

21:36.822 --> 21:38.054
I'd no idea
who they were.

21:38.056 --> 21:39.656
Let me ask you a question.

21:39.658 --> 21:42.626
The character in the book
you call "Dean Keith"

21:42.628 --> 21:45.462
he didn't say
"Poor people bagels," did he?

21:45.464 --> 21:46.830
<i>I think I know who he is.</i>

21:46.832 --> 21:47.997
<i>I think I know
a real estate lawyer</i>

21:47.999 --> 21:49.299
that worked with him
and quit.

21:49.301 --> 21:50.667
He said...

21:50.669 --> 21:52.104
"Nigger bagels," right?

21:58.110 --> 22:00.010
I'm not telling you his real
name. He's not involved in this.

22:00.012 --> 22:02.148
But you were willing
to name some names.

22:08.687 --> 22:10.320
Why is the FBI arresting me

22:10.322 --> 22:11.821
two years after
I stopped running games?

22:11.823 --> 22:13.991
Were you paid extra
in your book deal

22:13.993 --> 22:15.595
to name the movie stars?

22:18.997 --> 22:21.397
I'm not your guy, Molly.

22:21.399 --> 22:24.670
I wish you good luck,
but this just isn't for me.

22:34.480 --> 22:36.679
I didn't know
who the Russians were.

22:36.681 --> 22:39.081
<i>I can get you
the $250,000.</i>

22:39.083 --> 22:40.551
I left 10 times
that on the street.

22:40.553 --> 22:41.651
It'll just take some time.

22:41.653 --> 22:42.886
We regularly lend out our best

22:42.888 --> 22:45.188
litigators like me to the ACLU

22:45.190 --> 22:47.590
Southern Poverty Law Center,
veterans groups.

22:47.592 --> 22:49.827
But I don't think
I can convince my partners

22:49.829 --> 22:51.962
to take a flyer
on "The Poker Princess."

22:51.964 --> 22:53.763
I didn't name myself
"The Poker Princess."

22:53.765 --> 22:57.099
Uh, "Molly Bloom, the self
proclaimed Poker Princess..."

22:57.101 --> 22:58.268
Is that "Us Weekly?"

22:58.270 --> 22:59.903
Yeah, I would agree
it would be unusual

22:59.905 --> 23:01.839
for them to print
something that wasn't true.

23:01.841 --> 23:03.307
But it's not true,
and if you think

23:03.309 --> 23:06.009
a Princess can do what I did,
you're incorrect.

23:06.011 --> 23:07.578
<i>I'm getting you don't
think much of me.</i>

23:07.580 --> 23:09.580
But what if every one
of your ill-informed

23:09.582 --> 23:11.581
unsophisticated opinions
about me were wrong?

23:11.583 --> 23:12.916
- I'd be amazed.
- Yeah. You know what, bud?

23:12.918 --> 23:14.485
- You would.
- You don't need me.

23:14.487 --> 23:17.457
- You need a publicist.
- No, I need a fucking lawyer!

23:24.396 --> 23:26.032
You didn't answer my question.

23:28.833 --> 23:30.570
When was the last time
you slept?

23:33.572 --> 23:35.041
It was a while ago.

23:43.515 --> 23:45.282
Alright.

23:45.284 --> 23:46.949
I'm gonna walk you through
the arraignment this morning

23:46.951 --> 23:48.385
'cause you shouldn't
do that alone.

23:48.387 --> 23:50.353
I'm gonna put some bodies
on you and walk you

23:50.355 --> 23:52.388
through the side door,
'cause I don't know

23:52.390 --> 23:53.423
what you've got on the Russians.

23:53.425 --> 23:54.925
But neither do they.

23:54.927 --> 23:56.693
And the Russians
take care of shit.

23:56.695 --> 23:58.231
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

24:01.033 --> 24:02.101
Yes.

24:07.739 --> 24:10.706
Almost. You gotta keep
your eyes up, alright?

24:10.708 --> 24:12.242
Always gotta look ahead.

24:12.244 --> 24:13.276
If you look down

24:13.278 --> 24:14.513
that's where
you're gonna go.

24:16.348 --> 24:17.580
Alright?

24:17.582 --> 24:18.814
If you look down

24:18.816 --> 24:20.951
that's where you'll go,
alright?

24:20.953 --> 24:22.789
- Yeah.
- Alright.

24:25.457 --> 24:26.924
Let's go.

24:26.926 --> 24:28.425
<i>My father's a therapist</i>

24:28.427 --> 24:30.560
<i>and psychology professor
at Colorado State.</i>

24:30.562 --> 24:31.994
No! No!

24:31.996 --> 24:33.062
<i>The second rule of his house</i>

24:33.064 --> 24:34.630
<i>is that academic excellence</i>

24:34.632 --> 24:36.667
<i>and athletic excellence
weren't optional.</i>

24:36.669 --> 24:38.834
You can't be afraid of it,
alright?

24:38.836 --> 24:40.570
Don't play defense.

24:40.572 --> 24:41.705
<i>And the first rule</i>

24:41.707 --> 24:42.973
<i>was that he made all the rules.</i>

24:42.975 --> 24:43.840
Again.

24:43.842 --> 24:45.574
Dad, I'm pretty tired.

24:45.576 --> 24:47.610
Hon, she's tired.

24:47.612 --> 24:49.545
We've been out here
since 6 o'clock.

24:49.547 --> 24:51.016
<i>Her lips are blue.</i>

24:52.383 --> 24:54.019
- You're tired?
- Yeah.

24:57.288 --> 24:58.757
What's another word for tired?

25:00.793 --> 25:03.630
Name a synonym for tired
and we'll get in the car.

25:04.697 --> 25:06.163
Weak.

25:06.165 --> 25:07.830
That's right.

25:07.832 --> 25:09.067
Let's go home.

25:09.701 --> 25:11.901
Again.

25:11.903 --> 25:14.370
<i>I decided to postpone
law school another year.</i>

25:14.372 --> 25:16.540
<i>After six weeks of tips,
I went to Barneys</i>

25:16.542 --> 25:19.476
<i>and asked for a dress that made
me look nothing like myself.</i>

25:19.478 --> 25:21.410
<i>I'd overheard stories
about games that folded</i>

25:21.412 --> 25:24.880
<i>after one bad night and I
needed this one to keep going.</i>

25:24.882 --> 25:27.283
<i>And I needed to bring
value to it.</i>

25:27.285 --> 25:29.453
<i>I knew if I
wanted to cement my place</i>

25:29.455 --> 25:31.320
<i>there was one guy I needed
to team up with.</i>

25:31.322 --> 25:32.489
Ten thousand.

25:32.491 --> 25:34.157
<i>And that was this man.</i>

25:34.159 --> 25:36.592
<i>The game had regulars
and the game had guests.</i>

25:36.594 --> 25:38.861
<i>And four of the regulars
were famous actors.</i>

25:38.863 --> 25:40.797
<i>And I'm gonna call one of them
Player X.</i>

25:40.799 --> 25:42.064
I'm all in.

25:42.066 --> 25:43.132
<i>Player X subscribed</i>

25:43.134 --> 25:44.701
<i>to the belief that money won</i>

25:44.703 --> 25:46.203
<i>was twice as good
as money earned.</i>

25:46.205 --> 25:48.905
<i>He lived to beat people
and take their money.</i>

25:48.907 --> 25:50.639
<i>Here's Player X
talking to one of the guests</i>

25:50.641 --> 25:51.907
<i>into folding the winning hand.</i>

25:51.909 --> 25:54.276
I swear on... look at me.

