- Yeah.
- No.

29:47.111 --> 29:48.744
I'm saying it means
on your behalf.

29:48.746 --> 29:49.945
I am appearing on your behalf.

29:49.947 --> 29:50.981
<i>In propria persona means</i>

29:50.983 --> 29:52.514
you're appearing on your behalf.

29:52.516 --> 29:53.852
Not my behalf.

29:55.454 --> 29:57.954
I'll check that out,
but the point is...

29:57.956 --> 29:59.321
I'm not your lawyer.

29:59.323 --> 30:01.326
And I'll make that clear
for the record.

30:19.945 --> 30:22.012
That's us over there.

30:22.014 --> 30:23.713
You know, why don't you
sit there?

30:23.715 --> 30:25.217
And you sit on the other side.

30:32.323 --> 30:35.324
You've gotta good judge.
He's a good guy.

30:35.326 --> 30:38.194
- <i>Counsel, please...</i>
- How about the prosecutor?

30:38.196 --> 30:40.030
<i>Good morning, Your
Honor, Harrison Wellstone</i>

30:40.032 --> 30:42.432
<i>Assistant U.S. Attorney
for the Southern District</i>

30:42.434 --> 30:44.734
<i>joined at counsel table
by Assistant U.S. Attorney</i>

30:44.736 --> 30:48.905
<i>Eric Brennan and FBI
Special Agent Deborah D'Angelo.</i>

30:48.907 --> 30:50.372
Thank you.

30:50.374 --> 30:52.574
<i>Are there any oral motions
at this time?</i>

30:52.576 --> 30:54.010
Switch with me.

30:56.180 --> 30:58.348
<i>On behalf of the defendant...</i>

30:58.350 --> 31:01.117
Just in case your lawyer
doesn't mention it

31:01.119 --> 31:02.452
next time you appear
in front of the judge

31:02.454 --> 31:05.422
you might wanna re-think
your clothes. Okay?

31:05.424 --> 31:07.494
You look like the Cinemax
version of yourself.

31:08.959 --> 31:10.926
I sold my clothes
when the government seized

31:10.928 --> 31:12.595
all of my money two years ago.

31:12.597 --> 31:15.165
Which, incidentally,
was the last time I ran a game.

31:15.167 --> 31:17.766
But I think
I already mentioned that.

31:17.768 --> 31:19.336
- Okay.
- <i>Not guilty.</i>

31:19.338 --> 31:20.736
<i>- Thank you, you may be seated.
- Hey. Switch back.</i>

31:20.738 --> 31:24.475
Defendant number two.
Nicholas Segel.

31:24.477 --> 31:26.943
Has the defendant seen
a copy of the indictment?

31:26.945 --> 31:28.278
<i>Yes, Your Honor.</i>

31:28.280 --> 31:29.779
Have you discussed it
with your lawyer?

31:29.781 --> 31:31.414
<i>Yes.</i>

31:31.416 --> 31:32.415
Switch back.

31:32.417 --> 31:33.917
<i>Yes.</i>

31:33.919 --> 31:36.552
<i>- And how do you plead?
- Not guilty.</i>

31:36.554 --> 31:38.620
Thank you,
you may have your seat.

31:38.622 --> 31:40.122
Your old boss.

31:40.124 --> 31:42.257
The one in the book
you called Dean Keith.

31:42.259 --> 31:43.827
He was terrible to you.

31:43.829 --> 31:45.794
Why cover up for him
by changing it

31:45.796 --> 31:47.429
to "poor people bagels?"

31:47.431 --> 31:50.032
I promise you
it couldn't matter less.

31:50.034 --> 31:52.569
<i>Has the defendant seen
a copy of the indictment?</i>

31:52.571 --> 31:55.871
- Just making conversation.
- <i>Yes, your honor.</i>

31:55.873 --> 31:58.174
- Hey, switch back.
- <i>Discussed with your lawyer?</i>

31:58.176 --> 32:01.211
<i>- I have.
- How do you plead this time?</i>

32:01.213 --> 32:02.579
<i>Not guilty.</i>

32:02.581 --> 32:04.347
<i>Have a seat.</i>

32:04.349 --> 32:07.282
Defendant number four.
Molly Bloom.

32:13.824 --> 32:16.393
Good morning, Your Honor.
Uh, Charles Jaffey

32:16.395 --> 32:19.065
for the defendant,
just for the purposes...

32:26.103 --> 32:28.937
Well, it's good to see you,
Mr. Jaffey.

32:28.939 --> 32:30.409
Are you with us this morning?

32:33.210 --> 32:35.244
Mr. Jaffey?

32:35.246 --> 32:38.580
Uh, yes, sir.
Just, uh, one moment.

32:38.582 --> 32:42.318
- Switch back.
- Seriously?

32:42.320 --> 32:44.620
You said you left ten times
that much on the street.

32:44.622 --> 32:48.590
In my office, when I said
the retainer was $250,000

32:48.592 --> 32:50.894
you said,
"I left ten times that much..."

32:50.896 --> 32:52.262
Yeah.

32:52.264 --> 32:54.563
Counsel! I need to record
your appearance.

32:54.565 --> 32:58.400
If it please the court,
Your Honor, Just one moment.

32:58.402 --> 33:00.669
You're extended credit,
you're destitute

33:00.671 --> 33:02.906
and you leave two and a half
million dollars on the street?

33:02.908 --> 33:04.440
I had to.

33:04.442 --> 33:05.908
<i>Didn't anyone try
to buy your debt sheet?</i>

33:05.910 --> 33:08.278
Everyone tried to buy my debt
sheet. Is this...

33:08.280 --> 33:10.847
Why didn't you sell it like
you sold your clothes?

33:10.849 --> 33:13.649
- I couldn't.
- Why?

33:13.651 --> 33:16.322
I couldn't be sure
how they were gonna collect.

33:19.591 --> 33:21.726
I was afraid
you were gonna say that.

33:26.931 --> 33:28.097
Counsel!

33:29.700 --> 33:30.699
Yes, your Honor. Uh...

33:30.701 --> 33:32.268
Charles Jaffey
for the defendant.

33:32.270 --> 33:33.735
For the purposes
of this hearing only?

33:33.737 --> 33:36.138
No, sir.
I am Molly Bloom's attorney.

33:36.140 --> 33:38.541
Uh, she's read the indictment,
discussed it with her lawyer.

33:38.543 --> 33:40.176
Waives the right
to have it read to her

33:40.178 --> 33:42.911
and pleads "Not guilty."

33:42.913 --> 33:44.880
Thank you, you may be seated.

33:44.882 --> 33:47.649
<i>Defendant number five!
Ilian Gershen!</i>

33:47.651 --> 33:49.686
<i>Good morning, Your Honor.</i>

33:49.688 --> 33:51.288
I'm gonna have to keep
reading your book.

33:54.024 --> 33:56.225
<i>There was a track
star of the 1930's</i>

33:56.227 --> 33:58.360
<i>named Matthew Robinson.</i>

33:58.362 --> 34:00.295
<i>Matthew Robinson shattered
the Olympic record</i>

34:00.297 --> 34:03.933
<i>in the 200
at the Berlin Games in 1936.</i>

34:03.935 --> 34:07.436
<i>Absolutely shattered
the Olympic record...</i>

34:07.438 --> 34:08.937
<i>and came in second.</i>

34:08.938 --> 34:11.840
<i>The man who came in first
was Jesse Owens.</i>

34:11.842 --> 34:13.909
<i>Jesse Owens went on
to be a legend.</i>

34:13.911 --> 34:16.110
<i>Matthew Robinson
went on to be a janitor</i>

34:16.112 --> 34:18.482
<i>at a whites-only
middle school in Pasadena.</i>

34:18.484 --> 34:21.583
<i>The difference
was 4/10 of a second.</i>

34:21.585 --> 34:22.985
<i>As if that wasn't enough</i>

34:22.987 --> 34:24.454
<i>Matthew Robinson
had a little brother</i>

34:24.456 --> 34:25.487
<i>who was also an athlete.</i>

34:25.489 --> 34:27.592
<i>His name was Jackie.</i>

34:28.525 --> 34:29.591
<i>I have two younger brothers</i>

34:29.592 --> 34:31.426
<i>who are overachievers as well.</i>

34:31.428 --> 34:33.862
<i>While I was ranked third
in North America</i>

34:33.864 --> 34:36.699
<i>my brother Jeremy
was number one in the world.</i>

34:36.701 --> 34:40.168
<i>And while I was placing into
AP Chemistry as a sophomore</i>

34:40.170 --> 34:41.603
<i>my brother Jordan was doing it</i>

34:41.605 --> 34:42.971
<i>when he was 12-years-old
or something.</i>

34:42.973 --> 34:44.507
<i>I don't know.</i>

34:44.509 --> 34:46.708
<i>I was a hot shot student
and a hot shot skier</i>

34:46.710 --> 34:48.744
<i>everywhere but my own house.</i>

34:48.746 --> 34:51.848
<i>As I got older, I began
to bait my father into fights</i>

34:51.850 --> 34:53.583
<i>without really knowing
why I was doing it.</i>

34:53.585 --> 34:55.654
What did everyone
learn in school today?

35:00.692 --> 35:03.192
Uh... I learned
that Sigmund Freud

35:03.194 --> 35:04.726
was both a misogynist
and an idiot.

35:04.728 --> 35:06.663
And anyone who relies
on his theories

35:06.665 --> 35:08.297
of human psychology is a quack.

35:08.299 --> 35:09.598
I don't know why you'd say that.

35:09.600 --> 35:11.668
You asked me what I
learned in school today.

35:11.670 --> 35:13.438
- Is this Mrs. Linwood?
- <i>Yup.</i>

35:14.538 --> 35:16.205
Did she happen
to mention anything

35:16.207 --> 35:18.174
about his work
on the unconscious mind?

35:18.176 --> 35:21.076
His dream analysis has
the credibility of a horoscope.

35:21.078 --> 35:22.679
But what got my attention

35:22.681 --> 35:24.980
was that he opposed the women's
emancipation movement.

35:24.982 --> 35:26.248
<i>He believed that a woman's life</i>

35:26.250 --> 35:27.616
is about her
reproductive functions.

35:27.618 --> 35:29.252
So you're really getting
to the nuts and bolts

35:29.254 --> 35:30.486
of why middle-class
suburban white girls

35:30.488 --> 35:31.654
have been oppressed
for centuries.

35:31.656 --> 35:32.855
No, Mrs. Linwood was just...

35:32.857 --> 35:36.192
Barbara Linwood
doesn't like men, Molly.

35:36.194 --> 35:38.594
She doesn't like dicks,
dad, there's a difference.

35:38.596 --> 35:39.864
Molly...

35:43.969 --> 35:45.634
Don't disrespect me
like that at the table.

35:45.636 --> 35:46.668
I wasn't disrespecting you.

35:46.670 --> 35:48.438
I was disrespecting Freud.

35:48.440 --> 35:49.739
And it's the kitchen table

35:49.741 --> 35:51.306
not the tomb
of the unknown soldier.

35:51.308 --> 35:53.576
And I'm a professional
psychologist, not a quack.

35:53.578 --> 35:55.011
- I never said you were...
- Yeah, you did.

35:55.013 --> 35:56.348
And don't do it again.

35:59.350 --> 36:01.049
And don't ever use language
like that again.

36:01.051 --> 36:03.719
Okay. Ignore my teachers,
watch my language

36:03.721 --> 36:05.420
and respect the kitchen table.

36:05.422 --> 36:06.656
What else do I
need to do before

36:06.658 --> 36:08.056
I'm allowed
to disagree with you?

36:08.058 --> 36:09.324
Make your own money

36:09.326 --> 36:12.027
so you can live
in your own house...

36:12.029 --> 36:13.498
and eat your own food.

36:16.400 --> 36:18.467
<i>I'd been running
the game for three years</i>

36:18.469 --> 36:21.136
<i>and saved $58,000.</i>

36:21.138 --> 36:22.772
<i>I was recruiting
and vetting players.</i>

36:22.774 --> 36:24.172
- <i>Keeping the books.</i>
- Call.

36:24.174 --> 36:25.641
<i>Collecting
and delivering checks.</i>

36:25.643 --> 36:27.076
<i>Meeting the needs
of all the players</i>

36:27.078 --> 36:28.511
<i>through out the week
and still working</i>

36:28.513 --> 36:30.078
<i>full time for Dean Keith.</i>

36:30.080 --> 36:32.348
<i>Who made it clear that
if I quit the office job</i>

36:32.350 --> 36:33.415
<i>I'd lose the game.</i>

36:33.417 --> 36:35.083
- Call.
- Eights, full of nines.

36:45.496 --> 36:46.895
I thought he had trips too.

36:46.897 --> 36:48.531
<i>He was slow-playing
into the river</i>

36:48.533 --> 36:50.500
and he hid the pocket eights
pretty well.

36:50.502 --> 36:52.235
It's a tough beat, man.

36:52.237 --> 36:54.673
- You owe the game...
- I know what I owe the game!

36:57.641 --> 36:58.741
I wanna talk to you a minute.

36:58.743 --> 37:00.208
- Okay.
- In the hall.

37:00.210 --> 37:03.479
<i>♪ It came from heartache ♪</i>

37:03.481 --> 37:06.081
<i>♪ Then it died ♪</i>

37:06.083 --> 37:08.987
<i>♪ From the street... ♪♪</i>

37:11.188 --> 37:12.524
Is he cheating?

37:13.658 --> 37:14.623
No.

37:14.625 --> 37:16.926
- How would you know?
- I'd know.

37:16.928 --> 37:18.261
He and Diego
aren't in bed together?

37:18.263 --> 37:19.565
No.

37:20.431 --> 37:22.498
What about him and you?

37:22.500 --> 37:23.965
A 52 card deck produces

37:23.967 --> 37:26.502
hundreds of millions
of random patterns.

37:26.504 --> 37:28.804
But every time one of you loses
two weeks in a row

37:28.806 --> 37:30.306
you're sure something fishy
is going on?

37:30.308 --> 37:31.543
Come on.

37:34.446 --> 37:36.746
I'm gonna stop paying you.

37:36.748 --> 37:40.049
- What do you mean?
- As my assistant.

37:40.051 --> 37:41.485
- Are you firing me?
- I'm not firing you.

37:41.487 --> 37:42.652
I'm just gonna stop paying you.

37:42.654 --> 37:44.020
You get paid once a week
from the game.

37:44.022 --> 37:45.420
It doesn't seem fair.

37:45.422 --> 37:46.822
But I also have a job working
for you 24 hours...

37:46.824 --> 37:48.824
And if you didn't have a job

37:48.826 --> 37:50.993
you wouldn't have the game.
You understand what I'm saying?

37:50.995 --> 37:52.994
I understand each of the words
that you're saying but I don't...

37:52.996 --> 37:55.732
- Look!
- 24 hours a day, every day.

37:55.734 --> 37:57.165
But you're gonna stop paying me
to do that job

37:57.167 --> 37:59.402
because I'm making too much
money doing my second job?

37:59.404 --> 38:01.170
And if I say no,
I'll lose both jobs?

38:01.172 --> 38:02.404
Because it doesn't seem fair?

38:02.406 --> 38:04.507
Business is bad right now.

38:04.509 --> 38:05.911
Welcome to the real world.

38:07.846 --> 38:10.513
Alright, here it is.
Banks are loaning you money.

38:10.515 --> 38:11.848
And they shouldn't.

38:11.850 --> 38:13.449
You're a bad risk, they know it.

38:13.451 --> 38:14.917
So the debt service
on your loans

38:14.919 --> 38:17.353
is close to 20%,
which is crazy.

38:17.355 --> 38:19.355
Twenty percent is
barely survivable

38:19.357 --> 38:20.757
if it's a bridge loan.

38:20.759 --> 38:22.391
But, like for instance

38:22.393 --> 38:25.527
it's taken you 10 years
to build seven houses.

38:25.529 --> 38:27.496
All of which are worth
less than they were

38:27.498 --> 38:29.565
before you built them,
because the housing market

38:29.567 --> 38:31.734
is on a downward trajectory
for the first time

38:31.736 --> 38:32.902
in the history of houses.

38:32.904 --> 38:35.472
And that's why business
is doing bad.

38:35.474 --> 38:38.174
Not because you're paying me
$450 a week.

38:38.176 --> 38:39.475
You're a business savant?

38:39.477 --> 38:40.942
I've read every piece of paper
in your office.

38:40.944 --> 38:42.645
You're making thousands
in tips every week.

38:42.647 --> 38:44.179
Why do you care about $450?

38:44.181 --> 38:45.982
Because I don't want to pick up
your dry cleaning for free!

38:45.984 --> 38:49.317
Well, you don't have
bargaining power here!

38:49.319 --> 38:51.890
You can refuse the pay cut
but you could lose the game.

38:53.924 --> 38:55.393
Cash me out, please.

38:57.094 --> 38:58.527
<i>I wasn't gonna wait for Dean</i>

38:58.529 --> 38:59.728
<i>to take the game away from me</i>

38:59.730 --> 39:02.098
<i>before I put a plan in place.</i>

39:02.100 --> 39:03.665
<i>The next morning,
I made appointments</i>

39:03.667 --> 39:05.467
<i>at the Four Seasons,
The Peninsula</i>

39:05.469 --> 39:07.071
<i>and the Beverly Hills Hotel.</i>

39:08.205 --> 39:11.339
<i>The suite was $5200 a night.</i>

39:11.341 --> 39:13.009
<i>I spent $17,000</i>

39:13.011 --> 39:15.677
<i>on a shuffle master that was
installed in the table.</i>

39:15.679 --> 39:17.712
<i>Faster, more reliable shuffles.</i>

39:17.714 --> 39:19.248
<i>Less downtime between hands.</i>

39:19.250 --> 39:20.917
<i>Food was brought in
from Mr. Chow</i>

39:20.919 --> 39:23.319
<i>and available to eat
on the side tables.</i>

39:23.321 --> 39:24.654
<i>There was Macallan 18</i>

39:24.656 --> 39:26.656
<i>Belvedere, 1942</i>

39:26.658 --> 39:29.090
<i>Remy Martin,
and a '88 Lafite Rothschild</i>

39:29.092 --> 39:32.094
<i>served by a bartender who'd
already memorized your drink.</i>

39:32.096 --> 39:35.130
<i>Cohibas and Monte Cristo
were in the humidor.</i>

39:35.132 --> 39:36.898
<i>A professional stylist
turned me</i>

39:36.900 --> 39:38.734
<i>into what my defense attorney
would later call</i>

39:38.736 --> 39:41.270
<i>"The Cinemax version
of myself."</i>

39:41.272 --> 39:43.572
<i>I spent almost everything
I had in preparation</i>

39:43.574 --> 39:45.040
<i>for the phone call
I knew was coming.</i>

39:51.181 --> 39:52.915
- Hello.
- <i>I want you to listen to me.</i>

39:52.917 --> 39:54.851
- <i>'Cause you need to hear this.</i>
- Where are you?

39:54.853 --> 39:57.085
<i>I need to tell you something
in plain English</i>

39:57.087 --> 39:58.654
<i>and I need to know
that you understood it.</i>

39:58.656 --> 40:01.190
- Dean.
- <i>You are unimportant.</i>

40:01.192 --> 40:02.625
<i>Do you hear me?</i>

40:02.627 --> 40:04.694
<i>And you are fired.</i>

40:04.696 --> 40:05.994
<i>The job, the game...</i>

40:05.996 --> 40:07.996
- <i>You're fired.</i>
- Can I ask why?

40:07.998 --> 40:09.998
<i>How many of my friends
are you sleeping with?</i>

40:10.000 --> 40:11.299
I'm not sleeping
with any of 'em.

40:11.301 --> 40:12.768
<i>That's not what I heard.</i>

40:12.770 --> 40:15.404
Listen to me.
With a HAZMAT suit, I wouldn't...

40:15.406 --> 40:17.074
<i>Can I give you some advice?</i>

40:18.275 --> 40:19.708
<i>Lose the bitchy air.</i>

40:19.710 --> 40:22.011
<i>Lose the superior air.</i>

40:22.013 --> 40:23.645
<i>And go to the office
and get your stuff</i>

40:23.647 --> 40:25.484
<i>and be out of there
before I show up.</i>

40:26.350 --> 40:27.785
Hey, are you Molly?

40:28.453 --> 40:29.552
Yeah.

40:29.554 --> 40:30.953
I'm Leah, um...

40:30.955 --> 40:33.022
Dean asked me
to pack your personals.

40:33.024 --> 40:34.056
I appreciate it.

40:34.058 --> 40:36.058
He also asked me
to get the numbers

40:36.060 --> 40:39.427
of tonight's players
so I can confirm the list.

40:39.429 --> 40:41.230
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>

40:41.232 --> 40:42.233
Don't be.

40:44.067 --> 40:45.567
My phone's in my car.

40:45.569 --> 40:46.802
Uh, I'll text you
all the numbers

40:46.804 --> 40:48.436
you need when I get downstairs.

40:48.438 --> 40:50.873
<i>I texted my replacement
a bunch of random numbers</i>

40:50.875 --> 40:52.241
<i>with 310 area codes.</i>

40:52.243 --> 40:53.342
<i>Then I sent a text</i>

40:53.344 --> 40:54.643
<i>to the players for tonight</i>

40:54.645 --> 40:56.145
<i>and told them
the game had been moved</i>

40:56.147 --> 40:59.882
<i>to the Four Seasons Hotel,
Suite 1401.</i>

40:59.884 --> 41:02.918
- Hey, how you doing?
- Drink?

41:02.920 --> 41:04.420
- Thank you very much.
- <i>Do you a part...</i>

41:04.422 --> 41:05.654
<i>I'd love to.</i>

41:05.656 --> 41:07.924
Yeah?
So this guy's producing it.

41:07.926 --> 41:09.458
You should, uh, come down.

41:09.460 --> 41:11.994
- Amazing.
- Yeah, it'll be fun.

41:24.908 --> 41:27.078
Fellas, can I have your
attention for a moment?

41:33.518 --> 41:34.686
Where's Dean?

41:36.386 --> 41:39.721
I'll be hosting a game in this
suite every Tuesday night.

41:39.723 --> 41:42.792
If you play tonight, you'll be
guaranteed a chair for a year.

41:42.794 --> 41:45.728
If you prefer to play
at the Cobra Lounge...

41:45.730 --> 41:47.866
there'll be no hard feelings.

41:53.737 --> 41:55.036
Let's play.

41:55.038 --> 41:56.605
<i>The game is mine now.</i>

41:56.607 --> 41:59.976
<i>I incorporated and Molly Bloom
Event Planning was born.</i>

41:59.978 --> 42:02.944
<i>I paid taxes and 1099'd
my employees.</i>

42:02.946 --> 42:05.348
<i>I never became romantically
or sexually involved</i>

42:05.350 --> 42:06.715
<i>with any of the players.</i>

42:06.717 --> 42:08.384
<i>The game would have
fallen apart.</i>

42:08.386 --> 42:11.219
<i>This was back when I was
still making good decisions.</i>

42:11.221 --> 42:12.922
<i>And I went to a lawyer
to make absolutely sure</i>

42:12.924 --> 42:14.723
<i>all this was legal.</i>

42:14.725 --> 42:16.257
<i>- Are you taking a rake?
- No.</i>

42:16.259 --> 42:18.127
Then you're not
breaking the law.

42:18.129 --> 42:19.862
- But can I give you advice?
- Please.

42:19.864 --> 42:21.364
<i>There's a saying
in my business.</i>

42:21.366 --> 42:24.232
Don't break the law
when you're breaking the law.

42:24.234 --> 42:26.569
- What do you mean?
- No drugs. No prostitutes.

42:26.571 --> 42:27.969
No muscle to collect debts.

42:27.971 --> 42:29.505
Oh, I don't do
anything like that.

42:29.507 --> 42:31.540
But you just said
I wasn't breaking the law.

42:31.542 --> 42:33.576
You wanna keep it that way
because you don't wanna

42:33.578 --> 42:35.259
break the law when
you're breaking the law.

42:36.346 --> 42:38.147
Am I breaking the law?

42:38.149 --> 42:39.315
Not really.

42:39.317 --> 42:41.417
We're able to find out
for sure, aren't we?

42:41.419 --> 42:42.685
Laws are written down.

42:42.687 --> 42:44.420
You're not taking
a percentage of the pot?

42:44.422 --> 42:45.621
No.

42:45.623 --> 42:48.190
You're running a square game.

42:48.192 --> 42:50.494
<i>My game had a tricky ecosystem.</i>

42:50.495 --> 42:52.027
<i>These guys could buy anything.</i>

42:52.029 --> 42:53.529
<i>But here, in this room</i>

42:53.531 --> 42:55.130
<i>you couldn't buy your win.</i>

42:55.132 --> 42:57.599
<i>You couldn't buy me,
you couldn't buy the girls.</i>

42:57.601 --> 43:00.002
<i>And you couldn't buy
a seat at the table.</i>

43:00.004 --> 43:02.638
<i>There's nothing as sweet
as a win you have to work for.</i>

43:02.640 --> 43:06.409
<i>And the wins and loses were
compelling, and they were real.</i>

43:06.411 --> 43:08.677
<i>Of course, it helped that the
players were gambling addicts.</i>

43:08.679 --> 43:10.148
Can I see you for a second?

43:16.020 --> 43:17.619
<i>Jay, you're famous.</i>

43:17.621 --> 43:19.654
You are an international
rock star.

43:19.656 --> 43:21.690
Oh, I wasn't sure
you'd noticed.

43:21.692 --> 43:23.292
You can't send
emails like that.

43:23.294 --> 43:25.393
Well, it's not a federal
production, okay?

43:25.395 --> 43:28.163
I just invited you to Cabo
for the weekend.

43:28.165 --> 43:30.532
The next woman you send
an email like that to

43:30.534 --> 43:31.634
is not gonna be me.

43:31.636 --> 43:33.402
It's going to be someone else.

43:33.404 --> 43:34.603
You're playing with fire.

43:34.605 --> 43:36.371
I'm telling you that
I'm in love with you

43:36.373 --> 43:38.873
and you are worried about me
getting blackmailed?

43:38.875 --> 43:41.009
Oh, my, that just makes me
more into you.

43:41.011 --> 43:43.746
Lemon head. They won't need
to blackmail you.

43:43.748 --> 43:46.181
They can get just as
much money from TMZ.

43:46.183 --> 43:48.284
And TMZ will give them
what they really want.

43:48.286 --> 43:49.918
Tell me the truth.
Was mine the first love letter

43:49.920 --> 43:50.953
you've gotten from a player?

43:50.955 --> 43:52.420
It was the seventh.

43:52.422 --> 43:53.855
All digitally transmitted.

43:53.857 --> 43:55.690
You are begging for
your life to be turned

43:55.692 --> 43:57.726
into a very public hell.

43:57.728 --> 43:59.094
So that's a no on Cabo?

43:59.096 --> 44:00.895
Why don't you just give your
wife and kids a break

44:00.897 --> 44:02.297
and run 'em over with a limo?

44:02.299 --> 44:04.232
I love the way that
you talk to me.

44:04.234 --> 44:05.235
Oh, God.

44:11.074 --> 44:12.907
- I've had a thought.
- Yeah?

44:12.909 --> 44:14.145
Raise the stakes.

44:17.047 --> 44:18.049
To what?

44:19.250 --> 44:22.254
50k buy-in. Blinds are 250/500.

44:25.388 --> 44:27.725
- That's a 500 percent hike.
- Yeah.

44:29.092 --> 44:30.494
I don't think it's a good idea.

44:30.495 --> 44:32.256
Could you guys give me
the room for a second?

44:34.265 --> 44:35.266
Sure.

44:40.404 --> 44:41.904
The players that are losing
a $100,000 a week

44:41.906 --> 44:43.304
are gonna be losing
half a million.

44:43.306 --> 44:44.839
The players winning
a $100,000 a week...

44:44.841 --> 44:46.674
Will have no one left
to play with.

44:46.676 --> 44:49.043
Players are gonna get hurt,
others are gonna get killed.

44:49.045 --> 44:51.045
And some will drop out.
It's not sustainable.

44:51.047 --> 44:52.216
We'll lose the game.

44:53.650 --> 44:55.016
Find new players.

44:55.018 --> 44:57.486
<i>He meant "Find new fish."</i>

44:57.488 --> 44:58.654
<i>I went recruiting again.</i>

44:58.656 --> 45:00.523
<i>First up was Donnie Silverman.</i>

45:00.525 --> 45:02.857
<i>Donnie won the World Series
of Poker last year</i>

45:02.859 --> 45:04.826
<i>and got in touch with me
through one of the players.</i>

45:04.828 --> 45:06.395
Are you fucking nuts?

45:06.397 --> 45:08.663
Donnie Silverman won
the World Series of Poker.

45:08.665 --> 45:10.098
You can watch it online.

45:10.100 --> 45:12.500
He took 11 hands
at the final table.

45:12.502 --> 45:14.969
But he had the nuts
on eight of them.

45:14.971 --> 45:17.239
And three of those...

45:17.241 --> 45:19.674
Three were two outers with
four players still in the hand.

45:19.676 --> 45:20.976
He ran hot.

45:20.978 --> 45:23.145
He doesn't lock his chips down,
he's reckless.

45:23.147 --> 45:26.581
He gives tons of action
and he's got $12 million.

45:31.355 --> 45:34.192
You know,
I don't like playing poker.

45:34.859 --> 45:35.991
Why do you play?

45:35.993 --> 45:38.060
I like destroying lives.

45:38.062 --> 45:39.264
Give him a chair.

45:40.797 --> 45:43.998
<i>The next recruit
was Brad Marion.</i>

45:44.000 --> 45:45.601
<i>Who everyone called Bad Brad</i>

45:45.603 --> 45:49.404
<i>because he was uniquely
terrible at this game.</i>

45:49.406 --> 45:51.839
<i>If there was a worse
player in the world</i>

45:51.841 --> 45:54.275
<i>Brad would still find a way
to lose to him.</i>

45:54.277 --> 45:56.277
Sorry, I don't have a chair,
but you're welcome to a drink.

45:56.279 --> 45:58.346
No, I just came to
introduce you to, uh, Brad...

45:58.348 --> 46:00.248
<i>I'm all in. Calling it.</i>

46:00.250 --> 46:02.083
- <i>Yeah, I call.</i>
- Sorry.

46:02.085 --> 46:03.719
I just wanted to introduce
you to Brad Marion.

46:03.721 --> 46:05.453
- <i>He wants to play.</i>
- Give me his information.

46:05.455 --> 46:07.422
- I'll check him out.
- Derek's gonna vouch for him.

46:07.424 --> 46:09.592
<i>"Derek's gonna vouch for him"
meant Derek would cover</i>

46:09.594 --> 46:13.298
<i>any losses if Brad didn't pay,
up to any amount.</i>

46:16.000 --> 46:17.799
- Hi, I'm Molly Bloom.
- Brad Marion.

46:17.801 --> 46:19.335
- Nice to meet you.
- You too.

46:19.337 --> 46:21.603
<i>But he could pay and had to.</i>

46:21.605 --> 46:24.505
<i>Because he embraced the fallacy
of being pot committed.</i>

46:24.507 --> 46:25.907
I'm all in.

46:25.909 --> 46:27.477
<i>You've already invested so much</i>

46:27.479 --> 46:30.980
<i>you might as well see it
through to the end.</i>

46:30.982 --> 46:33.514
<i>Bad Brad had raised
$700 million</i>

46:33.516 --> 46:36.384
<i>for a fund that traded
oil futures and every week</i>

46:36.386 --> 46:39.388
<i>he came to the game,
lost a $100,000 and tipped me</i>

46:39.390 --> 46:42.391
<i>five thousand so he could
play the next week.</i>

46:42.393 --> 46:44.627
<i>He wasn't getting any better...</i>

46:44.629 --> 46:46.364
<i>and the guys were
feasting on him.</i>

46:50.467 --> 46:52.534
Can I get another 50?

46:52.536 --> 46:54.873
- Can we talk for a second?
- Sure.

46:56.940 --> 46:58.273
Brad, this game might not
be for you.

46:58.275 --> 47:00.477
I know I'm no card shark.

47:00.479 --> 47:01.947
No, you're not.

47:04.382 --> 47:06.547
Here are your losses
after ten weeks.

47:06.549 --> 47:09.183
And you've won... never.

47:09.185 --> 47:11.552
It's actually
a statistical anomaly.

47:11.554 --> 47:13.024
Yeah. I know.

47:14.225 --> 47:15.290
I like playing with the guys.

47:15.292 --> 47:17.025
I don't have that many friends.

47:17.027 --> 47:19.060
Don't take my seat away.

47:19.062 --> 47:20.362
I can tip you more.

47:20.364 --> 47:21.897
No.

47:21.899 --> 47:23.299
Your tips are very generous.

47:23.301 --> 47:25.333
How about I-I get you
some books.

47:25.335 --> 47:27.935
Or even, even a pro
to give you lessons?

47:27.937 --> 47:30.505
Yeah, maybe.

47:30.507 --> 47:33.107
- Yeah, let me think about it.
- Okay.

47:33.109 --> 47:35.978
<i>Turned out Bad Brad
knew what he was doing.</i>

47:35.980 --> 47:37.479
<i>He was getting customers.</i>

47:37.481 --> 47:39.248
<i>He'd drop his
100K at the game</i>

47:39.250 --> 47:41.317
<i>and pick up four million
for his hedge fund.</i>

47:41.319 --> 47:43.085
- Tell him what's smart...
- Not me.

47:43.087 --> 47:45.054
<i>More on that later, but first</i>

47:45.056 --> 47:46.355
<i>Harlan Eustice.</i>

47:46.357 --> 47:47.690
<i>Player X said he met Harlan</i>

47:47.692 --> 47:49.058
<i>at the Commerce Casino</i>

47:49.060 --> 47:50.525
<i>and that he'd be
good for the game.</i>

47:50.527 --> 47:52.427
<i>But I wasn't seeing
what he was seeing.</i>

47:52.429 --> 47:56.297
<i>He played tight, folding after
the hole cards 64% of the time.</i>

47:56.299 --> 47:58.333
<i>It wasn't clear
where his money came from.</i>

47:58.335 --> 48:00.369
<i>He produced backyard
wrestling videos</i>

48:00.371 --> 48:02.270
<i>and other low-rent productions.</i>

48:02.272 --> 48:03.572
<i>But worst of all</i>

48:03.574 --> 48:06.174
<i>Harlan Eustice
was a good card player.</i>

48:06.176 --> 48:09.310
<i>Why would Player X want someone
at the game who could beat him?</i>

48:09.312 --> 48:12.014
<i>I learned the answer
to that one the hard way.</i>

48:12.016 --> 48:14.382
- How was your flight?
- Just fine.

48:14.384 --> 48:16.585
How are you paying for tickets
between L.A. and New York?

48:16.587 --> 48:18.619
I had two million points
left on my Amex.

48:18.621 --> 48:20.221
They took the card,
but let me keep the points.

48:20.223 --> 48:21.422
Which I thought
was nice of them.

48:21.424 --> 48:23.726
- You had meetings.
- Hmm?

48:23.728 --> 48:25.828
You had meetings in L.A.
about your book and life rights.

48:25.830 --> 48:27.061
- I did.
- Was there any interest?

48:27.063 --> 48:28.563
A company that owns
four thousand

48:28.565 --> 48:29.464
video poker machines

48:29.466 --> 48:31.165
wants to put my face on them.

48:31.167 --> 48:33.335
Anything else?

48:33.337 --> 48:35.136
"Treat Magazine"
made a generous offer.

48:35.138 --> 48:36.472
- "Treat?"
- It's a new magazine.

48:36.474 --> 48:38.273
For the high-end
photography enthusiast.

48:38.275 --> 48:40.375
- They want you to pose naked.
- I'd be the April treat.

48:40.377 --> 48:42.143
I meant interest in your book.

48:42.145 --> 48:44.045
Ah, yeah.

48:44.047 --> 48:46.982
- Any offers?
- A few, I guess.

48:46.984 --> 48:49.016
Couple...

48:49.018 --> 48:50.052
Five.

48:50.054 --> 48:51.420
- Really?
- Yeah.

48:51.422 --> 48:53.020
- And...
- I passed.

48:53.022 --> 48:54.422
You're destitute
and you passed on

48:54.424 --> 48:56.023
five offers to turn
your book into a movie.

48:56.025 --> 48:57.058
You will be paid, Charlie.

48:57.060 --> 48:58.226
I'm just curious as to why

48:58.228 --> 48:59.395
you passed on
what would appear to be

48:59.397 --> 49:01.330
the only way out you have.

49:01.332 --> 49:02.531
Creative differences.

49:02.533 --> 49:04.333
- Okay.
- Should we start?

49:04.335 --> 49:06.435
You know, I am gonna
figure you out.

49:06.437 --> 49:07.636
Well, let me know
what you find.

49:07.638 --> 49:11.038
You see this?
This is discovery.

49:11.040 --> 49:13.442
Let's see what we discovered.

49:13.444 --> 49:16.244
Over here we have
Peter Druzhinsky

49:16.246 --> 49:18.980
Peter Antonovich
and Peter Slobo.

49:18.982 --> 49:20.181
The three Petes.

49:20.183 --> 49:21.315
Now the three Petes run a chain

49:21.317 --> 49:22.784
of corrupt medical clinics

49:22.786 --> 49:24.920
<i>and have been committing
insurance fraud</i>

49:24.922 --> 49:28.156
wire fraud and mail fraud
on an epic scale.

49:28.158 --> 49:29.391
Now, over here we have

49:29.393 --> 49:32.560
the Ragnyada-Gershen
Organization.

49:32.562 --> 49:34.695
They're a worldwide
bookmaking operation

49:34.697 --> 49:37.098
handling hundreds of millions
of dollars a year

49:37.100 --> 49:38.699
in illegal sports betting.

49:38.701 --> 49:39.868
And over here, we have

49:39.870 --> 49:42.538
<i>the Alexander-Habib
Organization.</i>

49:42.540 --> 49:45.239
This is also an illegal
sports betting organization.

49:45.241 --> 49:48.310
But this one,
financed by an art gallery

49:48.312 --> 49:51.746
owned by Shillel Habib,
who everyone calls...

49:51.748 --> 49:53.217
Shelly.

49:56.953 --> 50:01.123
This is the Russian Mafia
and the three are tied together

50:01.125 --> 50:04.226
in the indictment through...

50:04.228 --> 50:05.397
a poker game.

50:06.529 --> 50:08.464
- Were they tapping my phones?
- No.

50:08.466 --> 50:09.498
<i>Thank God.</i>

50:09.500 --> 50:10.531
They were tapping the phones

50:10.533 --> 50:11.833
of everyone you talked to.

50:11.835 --> 50:13.201
<i>Okay.</i>

50:13.203 --> 50:14.969
They got you confirming
that you ran raked games

50:14.971 --> 50:17.605
at the Plaza Hotel and various
locations in New York.

50:17.607 --> 50:19.907
<i>They've also got
a confidential informant</i>

50:19.909 --> 50:22.643
confirming that you ran
raked games at the Plaza Hotel

50:22.645 --> 50:24.413
and various locations
in New York.

50:24.415 --> 50:28.116
You were in violation of 1955,
which is a part of the U.S. Code

50:28.118 --> 50:31.252
<i>that makes it illegal to run
an illegal gambling business.</i>

50:31.254 --> 50:32.753
<i>You know what you did?</i>

50:32.755 --> 50:35.089
You finished writing a book
before the good part happened.

50:35.091 --> 50:37.726
You really get a kick out
of yourself, don't you?

50:37.728 --> 50:39.728
You know,
I don't like this picture.

50:39.730 --> 50:41.362
- Thank you.
- <i>You're like the cat...</i>

50:41.364 --> 50:42.531
That ate the canary
and then told

50:42.533 --> 50:43.931
the canary's
parents about it.

50:43.933 --> 50:45.199
<i>It's the picture
the publisher wanted</i>

50:45.201 --> 50:46.235
and I didn't get a vote.

50:46.237 --> 50:47.636
I liked the book, good story.

50:47.638 --> 50:49.003
- Well told.
- Thank you.

50:49.005 --> 50:50.272
I need you to tell
it again, though.

50:50.274 --> 50:51.406
From the beginning,
and this time

50:51.408 --> 50:53.074
without skipping over
the Russians.

50:53.076 --> 50:54.409
<i>Would you
like a glass of water?</i>

50:54.411 --> 50:56.246
I'd like a glass of Bourbon.

50:59.149 --> 51:01.215
- One more thing.
- <i>Yeah?</i>

51:01.217 --> 51:02.583
I need your hard drives.

51:02.585 --> 51:04.152
- Going back how far?
- What do you mean?

51:04.154 --> 51:06.955
Well, I kept my hard drives
when I'd buy a new laptop.

51:06.957 --> 51:08.123
- You're kidding.
- No.

51:08.125 --> 51:09.424
It had a record of who owed what

51:09.426 --> 51:10.458
and spreadsheets on the players.

51:10.460 --> 51:11.592
<i>It has more than that.</i>

51:11.594 --> 51:12.994
Every time you charge your phone

51:12.996 --> 51:14.563
by plugging it into the computer

51:14.565 --> 51:15.998
the computer takes a record

51:16.000 --> 51:17.866
<i>of all your text messages
and emails.</i>

51:17.868 --> 51:20.335
My laptop has a record
of all text messages and emails

51:20.337 --> 51:21.837
received years ago on phones

51:21.839 --> 51:23.538
that have been smashed
with an aluminum bat?

51:23.540 --> 51:26.607
I wanna run a forensic imaging
on your hard drives.

51:26.609 --> 51:28.710
Oh, no. Thanks anyway, but I'll
be destroying those hard drives.

51:28.712 --> 51:30.444
No, you can't do that,
they're evidence.

51:30.446 --> 51:31.880
I'm going to blow them up,
I am literally gonna use

51:31.882 --> 51:33.483
explosives and scatter
the remains in the sea.

51:33.485 --> 51:35.349
Except you told me they exist.

51:35.351 --> 51:36.486
You're gonna have
to pretend I didn't tell you.

51:36.488 --> 51:37.953
- Can't do that.
- Yes, you can.

51:37.955 --> 51:39.054
<i>You wanted a lawyer that</i>

51:39.056 --> 51:40.389
wasn't even a little bit shady.

51:40.391 --> 51:41.556
New information
has come to light.

51:41.558 --> 51:42.590
- I see that was stupid.
- Molly.

51:42.592 --> 51:43.926
There are no hard drives.

51:43.928 --> 51:45.627
If you destroy evidence
and obstruct justice

51:45.629 --> 51:47.462
on top of the charges
already brought against you

51:47.464 --> 51:50.165
in this case, you will be,
I promise, incarcerated.

51:50.167 --> 51:52.601
You don't understand
what's in those text messages.

51:52.603 --> 51:54.536
I understand you've had
boyfriends and there'll be

51:54.538 --> 51:56.572
some exchanges that are a little
bit, you know, embarrassing...

51:56.574 --> 51:59.308
I don't care about embarrassing
text messages from boyfriends

51:59.310 --> 52:01.076
as there is not left
the smallest corner

52:01.078 --> 52:02.411
of my private life

52:02.413 --> 52:04.712
that isn't available
for public scrutiny.

52:04.714 --> 52:07.516
There are messages that
would destroy other lives.

52:07.518 --> 52:09.284
<i>There are messages
that would end careers</i>

52:09.286 --> 52:10.786
and obliterate families.

52:10.788 --> 52:13.522
If those the text messages
were to be made public...

52:13.524 --> 52:14.922
- They won't be.
- If they were...

52:14.924 --> 52:17.259
- They won't be.
- It would be catastrophic.

52:17.261 --> 52:18.694
- I'm a lawyer, I'm legally...
- No.

52:18.696 --> 52:20.895
Listen to me,
I am legally prohibited

52:20.897 --> 52:21.897
from disclosing anything...

52:21.899 --> 52:23.331
Someone leaked
my last deposition

52:23.333 --> 52:24.933
to the National Enquirer,
Charlie.

52:24.935 --> 52:26.534
- Butterball?
- My last lawyer's name...

52:26.536 --> 52:28.536
Was Butterman
and he was one of five people

52:28.538 --> 52:30.371
in the room besides me.

52:30.373 --> 52:31.906
But the information
in that deposition

52:31.908 --> 52:34.409
will be nothing compared
to the consequences

52:34.411 --> 52:35.944
of those text messages...

52:35.946 --> 52:38.513
Ah! I just got it.

52:38.515 --> 52:39.648
Showing up everywhere.

52:39.650 --> 52:41.248
I couldn't figure out why you

52:41.250 --> 52:43.085
named some people
but not others.

52:43.087 --> 52:44.953
I thought that maybe
some people paid you.

52:44.955 --> 52:46.822
You were wrong.
But doesn't matter.

52:46.824 --> 52:48.956
No, the only people you named
in that book were the ones

52:48.958 --> 52:52.293
that were already named in
the Bad Brad Marion deposition.

52:52.295 --> 52:53.661
- Which you think...
- I know.

52:53.663 --> 52:54.929
- Somebody leaked it.
- Sold it.

52:54.931 --> 52:56.264
- <i>To the tabloids.</i>
- Yes.

52:56.266 --> 52:57.665
- Maybe even Butterbean.
- Butterman.

52:57.667 --> 52:59.000
But I don't know who it was.

52:59.002 --> 53:00.268
I watched Jenny McCarthy

53:00.270 --> 53:01.569
beat you up
for naming the players.

53:01.571 --> 53:02.670
Why didn't you just say,
"Hey, those names

53:02.672 --> 53:04.339
are already public record?"

53:04.341 --> 53:07.275
I don't know. 'Cause I wasn't
on "The View" under subpoena.

53:07.277 --> 53:09.377
Can we please get back
to the emails and texts?

53:09.379 --> 53:10.978
Is that why you have
creative differences

53:10.980 --> 53:12.014
with the Hollywood offers?

53:12.016 --> 53:13.281
<i>Because they want information</i>

53:13.283 --> 53:14.449
<i>and you won't give them.</i>

53:14.451 --> 53:15.485
- I don't know you.
- <i>Hm.</i>

53:15.487 --> 53:16.518
If what happened last time

53:16.520 --> 53:17.918
were to happen this time

53:17.920 --> 53:20.188
it would make
what happened last time...

53:20.190 --> 53:21.490
What is this for?

53:21.492 --> 53:23.357
It's got every text message
and email

53:23.359 --> 53:25.694
I sent in the last year
as well as a variety

53:25.696 --> 53:27.728
of incriminating evidence
about my clients.

53:27.730 --> 53:29.331
Now if anything
of yours get leaked

53:29.333 --> 53:31.732
you can sell my phone
to the highest bidder

53:31.734 --> 53:34.402
and I'll lose my job
and get disbarred.

53:34.404 --> 53:36.270
So in order to demonstrate
the sanctity

53:36.272 --> 53:38.339
of your attorney-client
confidentiality

53:38.341 --> 53:40.342
you're betraying
the confidentiality

53:40.344 --> 53:41.546
of all your other clients?

53:42.812 --> 53:45.147
I know you're not
gonna look at it.

53:45.149 --> 53:46.915
How do you know?

53:46.917 --> 53:47.919
I don't know.

53:54.223 --> 53:55.924
<i>I'll fly home to Colorado...</i>

53:55.926 --> 53:57.828
and be back the next day
with the hard drives.

54:00.397 --> 54:01.862
<i>Harlan Eustice was excited</i>

54:01.864 --> 54:03.831
<i>about the surprise
40th birthday party</i>

54:03.833 --> 54:06.134
<i>he was throwing for
his wife in 24 hours.</i>

54:06.136 --> 54:08.636
I rented out the whole
courtyard of the Buffalo Club.

54:08.638 --> 54:10.371
It'll be about a hundred people.

54:10.373 --> 54:13.074
Kumamoto oysters,
snow crab, lobsters.

54:13.076 --> 54:15.610
<i>He wasn't taking off
menu items to show off.</i>

54:15.612 --> 54:17.378
<i>He was genuinely excited
about the party</i>

54:17.380 --> 54:18.612
<i>he was giving his wife.</i>

54:18.614 --> 54:19.781
She doesn't know
anything about it.

54:19.783 --> 54:20.815
She thinks we're having dinner

54:20.817 --> 54:23.486
with her brother and his wife.

54:23.488 --> 54:24.985
<i>I liked Harlan.</i>

54:24.987 --> 54:27.490
<i>But nobody else liked him
except Player X.</i>

54:27.492 --> 54:29.257
- <i>He played tight.</i>
- Fold

54:29.259 --> 54:30.792
<i>Didn't give a lot of action</i>

54:30.794 --> 54:32.594
<i>and always got
his money in good.</i>

54:32.596 --> 54:34.429
<i>Which means he was
running the odds.</i>

54:34.431 --> 54:36.230
- <i>Five thousand to call.</i>
- No.

54:36.232 --> 54:38.766
<i>In other words,
he was playing poker.</i>

54:38.768 --> 54:40.504
<i>And the others were gambling.</i>

54:43.172 --> 54:44.408
<i>And he won.</i>

54:45.676 --> 54:48.176
<i>By midnight, Harlan had
tripled his original</i>

54:48.178 --> 54:50.177
<i>fifty thousand dollar buy-in.</i>

54:50.179 --> 54:53.248
<i>But everything came off
the rails with one hand.</i>

54:53.250 --> 54:54.616
<i>And that's how it happens.</i>

54:54.618 --> 54:56.618
<i>That's how you go full-tilt.</i>

54:56.620 --> 54:58.920
<i>Harlan, the best player
at the table</i>

54:58.922 --> 55:01.723
<i>the best player at most
tables was about to get</i>

55:01.725 --> 55:04.558
<i>bluffed off the win by,
of all people...</i>

55:04.560 --> 55:07.261
<i>Bad Brad. How?</i>

55:07.263 --> 55:09.964
<i>Because Harlan had never
played with Brad before</i>

55:09.966 --> 55:13.802
<i>and didn't know yet
that Brad was bad.</i>

55:13.804 --> 55:17.205
<i>Harlan's got a boat.
9's full.</i>

55:17.207 --> 55:18.672
<i>Brad's got nothing.</i>

55:18.674 --> 55:20.241
<i>But his pre-flop
betting made it look</i>

55:20.243 --> 55:22.810
<i>entirely accidently,
like there was</i>

55:22.812 --> 55:24.078
<i>a chance he had pocket kings.</i>

55:24.080 --> 55:25.279
Twenty thousand.

55:25.281 --> 55:26.614
<i>Which if true</i>

55:26.616 --> 55:29.284
<i>would give him
the better full house.</i>

55:29.286 --> 55:32.186
<i>Brad's counting off $20,000,
which means he's going to call</i>

55:32.188 --> 55:35.056
<i>and Harlan knows that if
Brad's gonna call and not raise</i>

55:35.058 --> 55:36.724
<i>it means he didn't
have the boat.</i>

55:36.726 --> 55:38.360
<i>And he's betting
a high two pair.</i>

55:38.362 --> 55:40.694
<i>Probably kings and queens.</i>

55:40.696 --> 55:42.496
<i>But then instead
of calling the bet</i>

55:42.498 --> 55:44.866
<i>Brad pushes $72,000
into the pot.</i>

55:44.868 --> 55:45.902
I'm all in.

55:47.103 --> 55:48.869
<i>Harlan looks at Brad.</i>

55:48.871 --> 55:50.772
<i>Every tell Harlan knows about</i>

55:50.774 --> 55:53.741
<i>carotid artery pumping,
stiff hands...</i>

55:53.743 --> 55:55.777
<i>Brad's doing the opposite.</i>

55:55.779 --> 55:57.712
<i>Brad's betting represented
a huge hand</i>

55:57.714 --> 55:59.147
<i>by calling on the flop</i>

55:59.149 --> 56:01.483
<i>check raising the turn
and bombing the river.</i>

56:01.485 --> 56:02.984
<i>Of course, Harlan didn't know</i>

56:02.986 --> 56:05.753
<i>that Brad didn't know
what any of that meant.</i>

56:05.755 --> 56:08.290
<i>So Harlan, always
a good sport said...</i>

56:08.292 --> 56:10.292
Nice bet. I'm laying this down.

56:10.294 --> 56:14.596
<i>As he tossed in what he
didn't realize was the winning hand</i>

56:14.598 --> 56:16.364
<i>Brad tosses in his cards too</i>

56:16.366 --> 56:18.599
<i>and one of them flips
over and Harlan sees...</i>

56:18.601 --> 56:21.703
You didn't have pocket kings?

56:21.705 --> 56:22.737
I didn't have any kings

56:22.739 --> 56:24.940
except the one in the middle.

56:24.942 --> 56:28.076
- You had two pair?
- I had one pair.

56:28.078 --> 56:29.481
The nines in the middle.

56:37.987 --> 56:38.989
Thank you.

56:41.324 --> 56:43.391
<i>It wasn't even that
it was that much money.</i>

56:43.393 --> 56:46.527
<i>Harlan only lost
about $40,000 on the hand.</i>

56:46.529 --> 56:47.962
<i>But a circuit breaker blew</i>

56:47.964 --> 56:50.165
<i>and Harlan was
out for blood now.</i>

56:50.167 --> 56:52.266
<i>Everyone's.</i>

56:52.268 --> 56:54.668
<i>We have a
$112,000 on the table.</i>

56:54.670 --> 56:56.304
<i>You want another 50?</i>

56:56.306 --> 56:57.605
Give me another 100, please.

57:00.611 --> 57:02.543
Sign here for a 100,000.

57:02.545 --> 57:05.447
<i>By 5 a.m., Harlan
was down half a million.</i>

57:05.449 --> 57:07.581
<i>He'd abandoned everything
he knew about poker</i>

57:07.583 --> 57:09.049
<i>and was playing
like a frat kid</i>

57:09.051 --> 57:11.688
<i>swinging for a home run
on every hand.</i>

57:13.891 --> 57:16.324
- Another 100 please.
- Hey, bud...

57:16.326 --> 57:18.129
Molly, please. Let's go.

57:19.795 --> 57:21.265
<i>Sign here for a 100.</i>

57:30.774 --> 57:33.275
<i>Text messages were going
out letting everyone know</i>

57:33.277 --> 57:34.775
<i>Harlan was bleeding.</i>

57:34.777 --> 57:35.844
<i>Guys were coming by to play</i>

57:35.846 --> 57:37.411
<i>for a couple hours before work.</i>

57:37.413 --> 57:39.413
<i>They'd been losing
to him for months.</i>

57:39.415 --> 57:41.782
<i>Everyone wanted a check
from Harlan Eustice.</i>

57:41.784 --> 57:42.984
If you go home now you can have

57:42.986 --> 57:45.386
a few hours sleep
before Sheila's party.

57:45.388 --> 57:46.556
Soon.

57:48.091 --> 57:49.657
Come talk to me.

57:49.659 --> 57:51.795
Hi, guys.
Help yourself to some coffee.

57:56.500 --> 57:58.333
You're on tilt.

57:58.335 --> 57:59.668
Everybody knows it.

57:59.670 --> 58:00.735
You're playing
without the weapons

58:00.737 --> 58:01.939
you need to win.

58:02.705 --> 58:03.908
You're right.

58:04.808 --> 58:06.043
Alright, thank you.

58:06.810 --> 58:08.612
Just give me $500,000.

58:10.346 --> 58:11.913
I just gotta get back to even.

58:11.915 --> 58:13.348
<i>That should be the second line</i>

58:13.350 --> 58:15.049
<i>of every gambler's obit.</i>

58:15.051 --> 58:18.752
<i>Mr. Feldstein died while
trying to get back to even.</i>

58:18.754 --> 58:19.920
<i>Harlan never did.</i>

58:19.922 --> 58:21.188
<i>And he never got to his wife's</i>

58:21.190 --> 58:22.424
<i>birthday party.</i>

58:22.426 --> 58:25.025
<i>She filed for divorce
two days later.</i>

58:25.027 --> 58:27.295
<i>There was one last punch coming</i>

58:27.297 --> 58:29.300
<i>that would put Harlan
on the floor for good.</i>

58:31.100 --> 58:33.335
<i>Harlan was heads up against
a guy named Frederick</i>

58:33.337 --> 58:35.039
<i>who was Austrian royalty.</i>

58:37.074 --> 58:37.938
Call.

58:37.940 --> 58:39.741
<i>Harlan had pocket queens.</i>

58:39.743 --> 58:42.110
<i>His Excellency had ace king.</i>

58:42.112 --> 58:45.313
<i>They were both in 65K pre-flop.</i>

58:45.315 --> 58:46.781
<i>Flops queen seven-seven.</i>

58:46.783 --> 58:48.349
<i>Harlan has a full house again.</i>

58:48.351 --> 58:50.085
<i>Queens full of sevens.</i>

58:50.087 --> 58:52.686
<i>With three rounds of betting
in front of him...</i>

58:52.688 --> 58:54.324
<i>the Count has nothing.</i>

58:57.761 --> 59:00.127
- All in.
- And the Count goes all in.

59:00.129 --> 59:01.529
<i>He wants Harlan
to think he's got</i>

59:01.531 --> 59:02.730
<i>two more sevens under there.</i>

59:02.732 --> 59:04.366
- Call.
- <i>"Nope," says Harlan.</i>

59:04.368 --> 59:07.701
<i>He's not falling for this again
and he snap calls all in.</i>

59:07.703 --> 59:10.341
<i>There's $750,000 on the table.</i>

59:11.808 --> 59:15.310
<i>Diego burns a card
and deals a turn.</i>

59:15.312 --> 59:18.913
<i>A king. Otto Von Bismarck
now has two pair.</i>

59:18.915 --> 59:20.882
<i>Kings and sevens.</i>

59:20.884 --> 59:23.384
<i>But two pair is nothing
next to a full house.</i>

59:23.386 --> 59:24.685
<i>And at this point</i>

59:24.687 --> 59:25.886
<i>the only hand left that can</i>

59:25.888 --> 59:27.657
<i>beat a queen full house...</i>

59:29.091 --> 59:30.794
<i>is a king full house.</i>

59:32.228 --> 59:35.429
<i>Captain Von Trapp
bluffed two pair</i>

59:35.431 --> 59:37.767
<i>and rivered into kings full.</i>

59:38.801 --> 59:40.567
Motherfucker!

59:40.569 --> 59:41.835
<i>Motherfucker!</i>

59:41.837 --> 59:43.938
- Fuck you, fucking mechanic.
- Hey!

59:43.940 --> 59:45.973
Fuck you, you bottom-dealing
party magician!

59:45.975 --> 59:47.442
Hey! Get out on the terrace.

59:47.444 --> 59:49.210
You've been pulling this shit
on me for two days!

59:49.212 --> 59:51.415
- Come on, come on.
- Party magician.

59:53.549 --> 59:55.419
- You good?
- I'm okay, thanks.

01:00:00.957 --> 01:00:02.790
<i>What the hell?</i>

01:00:02.792 --> 01:00:05.560
I'll apologize to Diego.

01:00:05.562 --> 01:00:07.529
Yeah. And you're gonna go home.

01:00:07.531 --> 01:00:09.199
I'm making a floor call,
that's it.

01:00:10.866 --> 01:00:12.035
<i>Did you hear me?</i>

01:00:13.335 --> 01:00:14.804
I don't have it.

01:00:18.542 --> 01:00:20.011
A million two.

